                  <origin> Allegedly completed by <persName role="scr ptr dub"
                        xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Aḥmad ‘Alī Kashmīrī</persName>
                     <origDate cert="low" calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1640">1050 AH (1640
                        CE)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance><p>While the circumstances under which this volume arrived in Britain
                        remain unclear, a prior European owner evidently acquired the manuscript on
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1819-12-09">9 Dec.
                     1819</date></p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Subsequntly obtained by Methodist theologian <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120696480" key="person_120696480">Adam Clarke
                           (1762–1832)</persName> from an unknown source.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p> After Clarke's death, his son <persName role="fmo"
                           key="person_79253656" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/79253656/">Jospeh
                           Butterworth Bulmer Clarke (d. 1855)</persName> inherited the volume and
                        describes it in his catalogue, no. 52, published in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1835">1835</date>.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>The next year, Clarke's son auctioned his father's collection
                        through the <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781"
                           >London</placeName> firm of <orgName role="auc"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/133731879" key="person_133731879">Sotheby &amp;
                           Son</orgName> on <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1836-06-20">20 Jun.
                           1836</date>, lot 121, where bookseller <persName role="bsl"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/34804600" key="person_34804600">William
                           Straker</persName> purchased the manuscript for £10.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Straker then probably sold the volume to scholar <persName
                           type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/"
                           key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803–1865)</persName> for the
                        latter's library at Randalls Park, <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011735" key="place_7011735"
                           >Leatherhead</placeName>.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>After Bland's death, <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781" key="place_7011781"
                           >London</placeName> bookseller <persName role="bsl"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5679225/" key="person_5679225">Bernard Quaritch
                           (1819–1899)</persName> sold his oriental manuscripts to <persName
                           role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058"
                           >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford (1812–1880)</persName> in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1866-06">June, 1866</date>, paid in two
                        instalments of £450 and £400, and then moved to <orgName
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/295427552" key="person_295427552">Bibliotheca
                           Lindesiana</orgName> at Haigh Hall, <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010384" key="place_7010384"
                           >Wigan</placeName>. </p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379"
                           change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/" key="person_9985420">James Ludovic
                           Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName key="person_f6379" change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta
                           Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1908"
